# Procedure Description {#procedure-description .unnumbered}

## Purpose/Objective/Scope {#purposeobjectivescope .unnumbered}

This process outlines the scope of the Aged Debtor Report at Starboard
Hotels.

## Input {#input .unnumbered}

-   Aged debtor reports from PMS systems -- For all 21 properties

-   PM report (Permanent Folio Report)

## Process Description {#process-description .unnumbered}

1.  The treasurer shares the current week folder with each GM to upload
    the relevant Aged Debtor reports and the PM reports

2.  Relevant GMs upload the relevant Aged Debtor reports to the folder
    by each Wednesday.

3.  Once all the reports are uploaded, check & verify that all the
    relevant reports are visible in the folder.

4.  Open the Aged Debt report summary file, copy the previous week's
    sheet, and rename it with the current week\'s ending date.

5.  Clear all the previous week's data column C to H in the new sheet.

6.  Open the hotel's aged balance report, check the values in column H
    (PM/Permanent Folios 2 days+)

7.  Copy all the notes (if any) from the Aged Balance report to the
    summary report.

8.  Once all hotels are updated, rename the summary report with the week
    ending date.

## Output {#output .unnumbered}

-   Completed Aged Debtor report (Weekly)

## Description of risks {#description-of-risks .unnumbered}

  -----------------------------------------------------------------------
  **Risk**                            **Mitigation Point**
  ----------------------------------- -----------------------------------
  Incorrect inputs. Incorrect         Include a Quality Check
  preparation of aged debtor reports  
  could lead to incorrect debtor      
  balances, which ultimately impact   
  the financial statements and        
  business decisions.                 

  Delay in inputs, delay in aged      Include a Quality Check
  reports could lead to delay in      
  taking business decisions and also  
  impact financial statements as      
  well.                               

  Duplicate inputs and duplicate      Include a Quality Check
  preparation of aged reports may     
  lead to overstated totals and       
  misleading week-on-week movements,  
  and ultimately to unnecessary       
  follow-ups and incorrect            
  conclusions in business decisions.  
  -----------------------------------------------------------------------

